cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT

This paper is about differentially private learning, which is a topic in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with privacy and security, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The adaptive clipping technique proposed in the paper involves computing a differentially private estimate, which involves statistical methods, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of model architecture and learning rate, which are topics in artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information theory, as it deals with differential privacy, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
